parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to retract properly can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the seat belt may not be able to properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt buckle will not fasten
the shoulder harness does not retract properly
false latching of the seat belt buckle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt buckle can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The bolt that holds the seat belt buckle is broken or cracked
the seat belt buckle will not fasten
both seatbelt buckles on rear seat belts will not fasten.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt cable can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the seat belt may not be able to properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: The cable that connects the seat belt to the floor of the truck is breaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rust Corrosion of Floor and Seat Belt Anchors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust corrosion of the floor and seat belt anchors can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential safety risks in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Rust holes in the floor
rusted seat belt anchors
exhaust fumes entering the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Exhaust System Failure (Warped Headers, Manifold, and Studs)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause a loss of power, decreased performance, and potentially lead to accidents due to reduced visibility caused by exhaust fumes.
symptoms: Ticking sound at cold starts
strong exhaust smells
noisy exhaust system
exhaust leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate design of the rear view mirrors can cause poor visibility, leading to blind spots that can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Reduced visibility
blind spots
inability to see vehicles or objects behind the vehicle
accidents or near-misses due to unseen vehicles or objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fire in the heater core housing can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from the heater core housing
burning smell
overheating
loss of heating or cooling functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accelerator pedal sticking can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal gets stuck
requiring physical force to become unstuck
causing the vehicle to accelerate to higher speeds
and making it difficult to control the vehicle's speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control becomes stuck
causing the vehicle to accelerate on an incline
and requiring the installation of a new cruise control unit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Irregular engine idling can cause unexpected acceleration, making it difficult to control the vehicle's speed, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The engine racing up and down at 1800 RPM when cold
then dropping to 900 RPM after 9 minutes
making it difficult to predict the vehicle's acceleration
and requiring the driver to be cautious when starting the vehicle.
